name: Kui'yang Krasue
description:
“ Is a folklore about a DEMON in the form of a HUMAN HEAD with body contents attached without skin and limbs 
that can fly to look for baby blood or WOMEN’S BLOOD after giving birth. This creature is known to the people of
Kalimantan. Kui’yang is told as a human (woman) who demands the teachings of black magic to achieve eternal life.”
